rengths:** Takes responsibility seriously, solves problems extremely well, can concentrate very well, and responds adequately to unexpected events.\n- **Weaknesses / Gaps:** No explicit evidence of calmness under pressure or decision\u2011making speed. Personality issues \u2013 arrogant, weak leadership, hot temper, moody, loner, know\u2011it\u2011all \u2013 are serious red flags for crew interaction on long\u2011haul flights. No weather\u2011assessment ability is mentioned.\n**Comparative assessment**\n- **Reliability:** B (explicit 100\u202f%) > C (very conscientious) > D (takes responsibility) > A (no data).\n- **Technical competence:** A (situational awareness, spatial vision) and C (complex\u2011technology understanding) are strong; B has solid weather\u2011assessment and computer skills; D excels at problem solving.\n- **Calmness under pressure:** B (keeps calm in crisis) and C (handles stress very well) are confirmed; D only \u201cresponds adequately\u201d; A has no data.\n- **Decision\u2011making speed:** C is the only candidate explicitly noted for quick, correct decisions.\n- **Teamwork/communication:** C creates a positive crew atmosphere despite communication difficulty; B\u2019s communication is overtly negative; A\u2019s leadership is marred by unfriendly/show\u2011off behavior; D is a loner and moody.\n- **Long\u2011term suitability:** C\u2019s conscientiousness and stress handling are strong, though his reluctance to further education is a drawback. B\u2019s reliability and calmness are excellent, but his interpersonal style could erode crew cohesion. A and D have multiple personality\u2011related weaknesses that make them less suitable for the high\u2011responsibility, collaborative environment of long\u2011distance operations.\n**Conclusion**\nWhen weighing all factors, Candidate\u202fC offers the most balanced profile for a long\u2011distance pilot: proven calmness under stress, rapid and accurate decision\u2011making, solid technical understandin