ling to further education (negative)\n- D: no mention of learning, but maybe weak leadership.\n\nOverall, which candidate best balances? B has reliability and calmness, but poor teamwork. C has good teamwork (positive atmosphere) but communication difficulty and unwillingness to further education. C also handles stress well, quick decisions, technical competence. B's technical competence includes weather assessment (critical). C also has technical competence. B's weak memory for numbers could be mitigated by automation but still a concern. C's egocentric and unwillingness to further education could be problematic for long-term adaptation.\n\nGiven the importance of crew coordination on long-haul flights, teamwork is crucial. B's negative behavior could degrade crew performance. C's communication difficulty is also a problem, but he creates positive atmosphere, maybe can improve. Also C is very conscientious, which suggests reliability.\n\nThus I might lean toward Candidate C as best overall, despite some weaknesses. However we need to consider calmness: C handles stress well, which is similar to calmness. Decision speed: C quick. Technical: understands complicated technology. Reliability: conscientious. Teamwork: positive atmosphere, though communication difficulty. Professional development: not willing to further education, but maybe not fatal.\n\nThus I will vote Candidate C.\n\nNow produce public message: include summary of attributes, reasoning, and vote.\n\nWe also need to incorporate the answer we got from tool (which is basically the same as Agent 1's answer). We can reference that we have no explicit info for those attributes.\n\nNow produce final."}
